Apple and Patreon
-----------------

From The Verge ( https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/12/24218629/patreon-member=
ship-ios-30-percent-apple-tax ) :

Patreon memberships sold on the iOS app will soon be subject to Apple=E2=80=
=99s 30 percent commission on in-app purchases. In a post on Monday, Patreo=
n says Apple is forcing the platform to use the company=E2=80=99s in-app pa=
yment system starting in November or =E2=80=9Crisk being kicked out of the =
App Store.=E2=80=9D As part of the change, creators will need to switch to =
Patreon=E2=80=99s subscription billing method to keep earning money through=
 the platform=E2=80=99s iOS app. That means Apple=E2=80=99s 30 percent comm=
ission will apply when a new membership is initially purchased, as well as =
each time it=E2=80=99s renewed. To help offset the costs of the new fee, Pa=
treon will give creators the option to automatically increase their prices =
in the iOS app.

This actually isn=E2=80=99t new news; Patreon announced that these changes =
were coming soon late last year ( https://news.patreon.com/articles/an-upda=
te-on-commerce-purchases-in-the-ios-app ). And honestly, I=E2=80=99m surpri=
